By Anthony Ada Abraham, Winner of the Big Brother Naija Season 5, Olamilekan Agbeleshe known as Laycon on Wednesday, was presented with his N30 million cheque which was broadcast live on DStv Channel 198. Laycon won a total prize worth N85 million. Other prizes include a two-bedroom apartment given by Revolution Home, a trip to Dublin sponsored by Guinness, among others. During the Q&A session, Laycon said he would be using his music to touch lives, put smiles on people’s faces. He said that was the main reason he went into the Big Brother House. It was also a win-win situation for MultiChoice and major sponsor, Betway as both confessed it was as rewarding to them as it was envisaged. 30 fans also got 1 million naira cash, courtesy of Betway. It would be recalled that Laycon became the winner of the 5th edition of the ‘Lockdown’ reality show on Sunday, defeating housemates Dorathy and Nengi to get the grand prize. Dorathy became the first runner up, while Nengi was the 2nd runner-up. During his media tour, after the show, Laycon spoke on his budding friendship with Kiddwaya which caught the attention of fans on social media. This was quite interesting and curious as Laycon was also interested in Kiddwaya’s on-screen bae, Erica. Laycon said that he honestly cannot explain how his friendship with Kiddwaya happened and that he even told Vee he was getting comfortable with Kidd and Erica situation because he liked Kiddwaya like a brother. 